# Data Pipeline Rules

## Column Aliases

Map all alternate names to canonical names in `normalize_aliases()`. Full alias map is in `DATA_SCHEMA.md` Section 11. Critical: `wAB → WAB`.

## Default Values

All defaults are fixed constants from `DATA_SCHEMA.md` Section 1.6. Zero randomness — no `random.random()` anywhere in ingestion.

## Overrides

- `overrides.json` format: `{"TeamName": {"mode": "delta"|"absolute", "AdjEM": -3.5, "note": "reason"}}`
- Set `OverrideActive = 1` flag on any team with active overrides.
- Apply overrides AFTER alias normalization and defaults, BEFORE scoring.

## Torvik / Massey Fetch

Use `cloudscraper.create_scraper().get()` — plain `requests.get()` returns 403 (Cloudflare). This is confirmed by live testing.

## Luck Metric

Always computed from Torvik data: `Luck = WinPct - Barthag`. No external dependency. This feeds Fraud Score at 25% weight.

## Data Validation

`validate_columns(df)` returns list of missing required columns. Empty list = clean. Surface clear error messages for missing/malformed data — never silently proceed with bad data.

## Input Files (never commit to git)

- `data/teams_input.csv` — primary input, one row per team
- `data/bracket_input.json` — post-bracket: seeds, regions, slots
- `data/overrides.json` — injury adjustments
- `.env` — environment config (optional)
